{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the agricultural IoT market is projected to grow at an annual rate of 20%, with applications extending to smart greenhouses, autonomous machinery, and advanced pest management systems, among others (Ayaz et al. 2019).",
    "Despite its potential, the adoption of IoT in agriculture faces significant challenges, including interoperability, scalability, high implementation costs, and regulatory barriers.",
    "Addressing these issues requires interdisciplinary collaboration among researchers, policymakers, and industry stakeholders to ensure equitable access and seamless integration across diverse agricultural landscapes (Torky and Hassanein 2020; Rejeb et al. 2022).",
    "Moreover, the environmental consciousness driving sustainable agriculture underscores the need for IoT solutions that minimize resource wastage and reduce pesticide use, aligning with global efforts to combat climate change (Bongiovanni and Lowenberg-DeBoer 2004; Kumari et al. 2024; Zanin et al. 2022).",
    "This review critically examines the transformative role of IoT in agriculture, focusing on three key objectives: (1) exploring types of agritech innovations and IoT applications; (2) summarizing mechanisms through which IoT enhances efficiency and sustainability; and"
  ]
}